+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LrshJdW7DvcSaGFLK2De9Z","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete understanding. Let me create a comprehensive report of the codebase and the failing tests.\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Exploration Report\n\n### Full Directory Structure\n\n**Source Files (10 files):**\n- `/workspace/src/index.ts` - Main export file\n- `/workspace/src/events/bus.ts` - Event Bus implementation\n- `/workspace/src/events/types.ts` - Event type definitions\n- `/workspace/src/orders/service.ts` - Order Service\n- `/workspace/src/orders/repository.ts` - Order Repository\n- `/workspace/src/inventory/service.ts` - Inventory Service\n- `/workspace/src/inventory/repository.ts` - Inventory Repository\n- `/workspace/src/billing/service.ts` - Billing Service\n- `/workspace/src/billing/calculator.ts` - Price calculation logic\n- `/workspace/src/notifications/service.ts` - Notification Service\n\n**Test Files (5 files):**\n- `/workspace/tests/events.test.ts` - EventBus tests\n- `/workspace/tests/orders.test.ts` - Order Service & Repository tests\n- `/workspace/tests/inventory.test.ts` - Inventory Service tests\n- `/workspace/tests/billing.test.ts` - Billing Service & calculation tests\n- `/workspace/tests/notifications.test.ts` - Notification Service tests\n\n---\n\n### Architecture Overview\n\nThis is an **event-driven order processing system** with these modules:\n\n1. **EventBus** (`src/events/`): Publish/Subscribe pattern with module-level handler registry\n2. **Orders** (`src/orders/`): Order lifecycle management with statuses: pending → confirmed → cancelled/refunded\n3. **Inventory** (`src/inventory/`): Stock management with reserve/release operations\n4. **Billing** (`src/billing/`): Payment processing and price calculations\n5. **Notifications** (`src/notifications/`): Confirmation, cancellation, and refund notices\n\n**Event Flow:**\n```\nOrder Creation:\ncreateOrder() → emit ORDER_CREATED \n  → InventoryService.handleOrderCreated() reserves stock\n  → BillingService.chargePayment() processes payment\n  → emit ORDER_CONFIRMED\n\nOrder Cancellation:\ncancelOrder() → emit ORDER_CANCELLED\n  → InventoryService.handleOrderCancelled() releases stock\n  → emit STOCK_RELEASED\n\nOrder Refund:\nrefundOrder() → emit ORDER_REFUNDED\n  → BillingService.handleRefund() updates payment status\n```\n\n---\n\n### Test Results Summary\n\n**Test Status:** 12 FAILED / 22 PASSED (34 total tests)\n\n**Failed Tests by Category:**\n\n#### 1. **OrderRepository Update Bug** (1 failure)\n- `OrderRepository > updates order preserves other fields`\n- **Issue:** `update()` method doesn't preserve existing fields (customerId, items, notes missing after update)\n\n#### 2. **OrderService Cancellation Bug** (3 failures)\n- `OrderService > cancels a confirmed order`\n- `OrderService > refuses to cancel a non-confirmed order`\n- `OrderService > refunds a cancelled order within 30 days`\n- **Issue:** `order.items` is undefined when trying to map over it in `cancelOrder()`\n\n#### 3. **Inventory Stock Depletion Bug** (4 failures)\n- `InventoryService > releases stock on order.cancelled`\n- `InventoryService > reserves stock for concurrent orders independently`\n- `OrderService > releases stock when order is cancelled`\n- `OrderService > rejects refund after 30-day window`\n- **Issue:** Stock gets unexpectedly depleted during cancellation test\n\n#### 4. **BillingService Binding Bug** (2 failures)\n- `BillingService > issues refund and updates payment status`\n- `BillingService > sends refund notification`\n- **Issue:** `this.payments` is undefined in `handleRefund()` - lost binding context\n\n#### 5. **Price Calculation Rounding Bug** (1 failure)\n- `calculateOrderTotal > handles multiple items with discount and tax`\n- **Issue:** Returns 130.87 instead of expected 130.86 (rounding error)\n\n#### 6. **Order Refund Status Bug** (1 failure)\n- `OrderService > allows refund on exactly day 30`\n- **Issue:** Refunded order returns undefined instead of the refunded order object\n\n---\n\n### Key Code Issues Identified\n\n**Bug 1 - OrderRepository.update()** (`src/orders/repository.ts:35-41`)\n```typescript\nupdate(id: string, updates: Partial<Order>): Order | undefined {\n  const existing = this.store.get(id);\n  if (!existing) return undefined;\n  const updated = { ...updates, id, updatedAt: Date.now() } as Order;  // BUG: doesn't spread existing!\n  this.store.set(id, updated);\n  return { ...updated };\n}\n```\nShould preserve existing fields with `{ ...existing, ...updates, ... }`\n\n**Bug 2 - BillingService.handleRefund()** (`src/billing/service.ts:25`)\n```typescript\nregisterHandlers(): void {\n  this.eventBus.on(ORDER_EVENTS.STOCK_RESERVED, this.handleStockReserved.bind(this));\n  this.eventBus.on(ORDER_EVENTS.REFUNDED, this.handleRefund);  // BUG: missing .bind(this)\n}\n```\nMissing `.bind(this)` on handleRefund loses context\n\n**Bug 3 - Price Calculation** (`src/billing/calculator.ts:20-22`)\n```typescript\nconst discountAmount = Math.round(subtotal * (discountPercent / 100) * 100) / 100;\nconst afterDiscount = Math.round((subtotal - discountAmount) * 100) / 100;\nconst taxAmount = Math.round(afterDiscount * taxRate * 100) / 100;\n```\nMultiple rounding operations cause accumulated rounding errors. Should round once at the end.\n\n**Bug 4 - InventoryService.handleOrderCancelled()** (`src/inventory/service.ts:42-62`)\nThe check for `eventWithItems.status !== 'cancelled'` at line 50 may prevent stock release. The CANCELLED event needs proper data passing from OrderService.\n\n**Bug 5 - OrderService.refundOrder()** (`src/orders/service.ts:105-108`)\n```typescript\nthis.repo.update(id, { status: 'refunded' });\nreturn this.repo.findById(id);  // Returns undefined due to update() bug\n```\nDepends on OrderRepository.update() fix\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\nThe system is an event-driven architecture with 5 major bugs causing 12 tes