/calculator.ts:20-22`)\n```typescript\nconst discountAmount = Math.round(subtotal * (discountPercent / 100) * 100) / 100;\nconst afterDiscount = Math.round((subtotal - discountAmount) * 100) / 100;\nconst taxAmount = Math.round(afterDiscount * taxRate * 100) / 100;\n```\nMultiple rounding operations cause accumulated rounding errors. Should round once at the end.\n\n**Bug 4 - InventoryService.handleOrderCancelled()** (`src/inventory/service.ts:42-62`)\nThe check for `eventWithItems.status !== 'cancelled'` at line 50 may prevent stock release. The CANCELLED event needs proper data passing from OrderService.\n\n**Bug 5 - OrderService.refundOrder()** (`src/orders/service.ts:105-108`)\n```typescript\nthis.repo.update(id, { status: 'refunded' });\nreturn this.repo.findById(id);  // Returns undefined due to update() bug\n```\nDepends on OrderRepository.update() fix\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\nThe system is an event-driven architecture with 5 major bugs causing 12 test failures:\n1. Missing property merge in repository update\n2. Lost `this` context in event handler binding\n3. Accumulative rounding in price calculations\n4. Stock release logic issue in cancellation\n5. Cascading failures from repository bug\n\nAll bugs are in the **source code only**—test files are correct and should not be modified."}],"totalDurationMs":28877,"totalTokens":34476,"totalToolUseCount":24,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4720,"cache_read_input_tokens":28040,"output_tokens":1709,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4720,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[]}}}
